properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 9 at 2:52AM CST until February 9 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...MODERATE TO HEAVY SNOW WILL IMPACT TRAVEL TODAY...

* WHAT...Heavy snow. Total snow accumulations of 5 to 8 inches.

* WHERE...Sheboygan and Dodge Counties.

* WHEN...From 9 AM this morning to 9 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Snow covered roads and limited visibility will
create difficult driving conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Be prepared to allow extra time to reach
your destination.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM THIS MORNING TO 9 PM CST THIS EVENING
